Introduction
************

Welcome  to TransAmiga BBS,  a Freeware bulletin board system (BBS) for
the Amiga.   TransAmiga's  aim  is  to  provide  an  easy  to setup and
use BBS program  for  not-so-demanding  tasks,  and  at  the same time,
incorporate flexibility  and  advanced  features  for  more  serious
purposes, such as networking and multi-line.

Installing  TransAmiga  for  the  first  time  is  made very easy using
the Installer  script.   All  necessary steps are taken to setup the
BBS so you can  run it without further configuration, though this would
be only a very limited  setup.   Customizing  the  BBS  is  too complex
to be handled by a script  so read this manual to gain full control
over the BBS.  You will be amazed by the possibilities TransAmiga has
to offer.

Please see @{"License" Link "License"} for the usage license.
Some familiarity with AmigaDOS, ARexx and general BBS terms is assumed.


 @{" TransAmiga Roots " Link "TransAmiga Roots"}             How TransAmiga came to life
 @{" Philosophy " Link "Philosophy"}                   The philosophy behind TransAmiga
 @{" System Requirements " Link "System Requirements"}          What you need to run TransAmiga
 @{" Features " Link "Features"}                     A short description of TransAmigas features
 @{" Registered vs. Unregistered " Link "Registered vs. Unregistered"}  What you obtain when registering TransAmiga


